title: Mike Whitehead Group plays Highlands
text:
Mike Whitehead Group plays Highlands Oct 09, 2015 
Thomaston — The Mike Whitehead Group will be back for another jazzy afternoon at the Highlands Coffee House, Main Street/Route 1, Sunday, Oct. 18, from 1 to 3 p.m. 
Band members include Mike Whitehead on trumpet and flugelhorn, Tom Luther on keyboards, Spike Hyssong on bass and Jason Dean on percussion. The combo, dedicated to the exploration of creative improvised music, plays a mix of original compositions and compositions by favorite artists. 
For more information, call 354-4162. 
Courier Publications’ A&E Editor Dagney C. Ernest can be reached at (207) 594-4401, ext. 115; or dernest@courierpublicationsllc.com.
